---
description: SQL migration safety for SECURITY DEFINER and schema changes
globs: supabase/migrations/**
---
Any new `SECURITY DEFINER` function MUST:
- `SET search_path = public` (prevent search-path hijack).
- Re-verify the caller's ownership/role INTERNALLY before mutating — do not trust an id passed
  by the caller (safe pattern: accept_offer re-checks traveler_requests.traveler_id).
Every migration MUST have a matching rollback in supabase/rollbacks/.
After any schema change, remind the operator to run `bun run types`
(regenerates src/lib/supabase/database.types.ts).
